  "body": "    what you need: Twelve sticks of length     Old pieces of paper    A pair of scissors.    A ruler    Pieces of string.    Join the twelve sticks to form a cube like the one shown on the right. use the pieces of paper to cover it to make a closed cube.    what is the volume of the cube you have made?    The cube you have made is called a cubic metre. It's sides are long.  The volume of the cube is      making cubes    Conversion of cubic metres to cubic centimetres.  Measure the length, the width and the height of the cube in metres . Work out it's volume in cubic metres.   Measure the length, the width and the height of the cube in centimetres. Work out it's volume in cubic centimetres.   How many cubic centimetres is one cubic metre? How can you convert the volume you got in cubic metres to cubic centimetres? Since   Therefore to convert volume from cubic metres to cubic centimetres, we multiply the volume by 1,000,000.  "
